positions.summary_lb:
Responsibilities
- Preparation and lodgement of tax returns, IAS and BAS for individuals, trusts and companies
- Compile year-end financial reports for small- medium enterprise
- Analyse client accounts and investigate any discrepancies and/or unreported movements
- Responsible for updating client asset transactions on share register for successful completion
of tax returns
- Evaluate and recommend appropriate tax treatment of transactions
- Liaise with ATO and ASIC on an ongoing basis
- Draft correspondence and provide professional reception to clients

Achievements
- Ability to prioritise and meet deadlines as a result of effective time management and
organisational skills, proven by an increase in work productivity
- Recommendations of appropriate tax treatment were approved by the director

Responsibilities
- Provided excellent customer service during peak Christmas season
- Assisted customers in ladies designer fashion and maintained store appearance
- Inventory control

Responsibilities
- Provided exceptional service by communicating with customers to identify their needs and
matched products accordingly
- Consistently built customer rapport through VIP membership
- Consistently met daily and weekly sales targets and responsible for store opening/closure
- Assisted with visual merchandising of products

Achievements
- Achieved the highest sale of the week across all Sydney stores
- Suggested merchandising popular stock on a roller-rack at the front of store which led to more
customer walk-ins

Responsibilities
- Provided customer service during peak Christmas season
- Built customer rapport through Myer One membership and Myer Visa
